      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI demonstrated to be directly predictive of hemolysis outcome relevant to COU decision.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) derived from scalar stress accumulation along pathlines is the primary QoI. RH is directly linked to the COU acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Sensitivity analysis confirms RH is responsive to the geometric variations under evaluation."
