    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters demonstrated to be equivalent to experimental conditions through documented parameter mapping and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "A comprehensive qualitative assessment of input parameter equivalency was conducted by the modeling team. Fluid viscosity, density, and inlet turbulence intensity were mapped from experimental documentation to simulation boundary conditions. The assessment reviewed each of the 14 primary input parameters against their experimental counterparts, confirming that the parameter space covered by the validation experiments is representative of the COU operating envelope. Engineering judgment by two independent reviewers confirmed that no systematic input discrepancies were identified that would materially affect the hemolysis index prediction. This qualitative equivalency review is considered sufficient to support the overall credibility determination at MRL 2, consistent with the proportionality principle in ASME V&V 40 Section 4."
    }
